  "prompt": "What does \"designation\" mean on a form?",
  "response": "The term \"designation\" on a form generally refers to the title, position, or rank of an individual within an organization or context. It specifies the official role or status held by the person filling out the form. For example, in a workplace setting, designation could be entries like \"Manager,\" \"Executive,\" \"Assistant,\" etc. It helps to identify the capacity in which a person is acting or applying.",
